27 March
- to connect to DO droplet via ssh
  - cd ~/.ssh
  - keygen-ssh
  - copy public key and paste on DO
  - ssh -i <private-key-file> root@<projectPublicIP> 

- to create DO cluster:
  Dashboard -> Create -> Kubernetes -> select most local CDN and basic node -> select your project -> create
  API -> create a token -> copy
  authenticate, cmd: doctl auth init
  paste the token when prompted
 
- change Kubernetes context with doctl:
  get connection to new cluster: 
  cmd: doctl kubernetes cluster kubeconfig save 

- list all contexts, 
  cmd: kubectl config view
- swap context:
  cmd: kubectl config use-context <context-name>